#: ../../B/blue-wire.rst:5
msgid "blue wire"
msgstr "blue wire"

#: ../../B/blue-wire.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../B/blue-wire.rst:9
msgid ""
"[IBM] Patch wires (esp. 30 AWG gauge) added to circuit boards at the factory"
" to correct design or fabrication problems. Blue wire is not necessarily "
"blue, the term describes function rather than color. These may be necessary "
"if there hasn't been time to design and qualify another board version. In "
"Great Britain this can be bodge wire, after mainstream slang bodge for a "
"clumsy improvisation or sloppy job of work. Compare :ref:`purple-wire`\\, "
":ref:`red-wire`\\, :ref:`yellow-wire`\\, :ref:`pink-wire`\\."
msgstr ""
"[IBM]設計や製造上の問題を是正するために工場で回路基板に加えられるパッチ用の配線(特に30 AWG規格のもの)。blue "
"wireは必ずしも青いとは限らない。この用語は色ではなく機能を表す。別の基板版を設計し認定する時間がなかった場合に必要になることがある。英国では、不器用な間に合わせやずさんな仕事を指す一般のスラングbodgeにちなんで、これをbodge"
" wireと呼ぶことがある。\\ :ref:`purple-wire`\\ 、\\ :ref:`red-wire`\\ 、\\ "
":ref:`yellow-wire`\\ 、\\ :ref:`pink-wire`\\ と比較せよ。"
